lot of claim holders

00:59:42.240 --> 00:59:43.250
whose money is invested.

00:59:43.250 --> 00:59:45.742
In other words,
corporations managers

00:59:45.742 --> 00:59:47.200
always invest other
people's money.

00:59:47.200 --> 00:59:49.920
The question is what does
these people have in return?

00:59:49.920 --> 00:59:52.590
A debt contract or an
inequity claim or what.

00:59:52.590 --> 00:59:55.664
Because banks have so much
debt, their shareholders

00:59:55.664 --> 00:59:57.830
become a little bit conflicted
with their creditors.

00:59:57.830 --> 01:00:00.330
Or the shareholders benefit
from government subsidies

01:00:00.330 --> 01:00:02.590
because they get
to borrow cheaply.

01:00:02.590 --> 01:00:06.920
So what ends up happening is
that at least the shareholders

01:00:06.920 --> 01:00:12.360
who count or their friends the
institutional investors that

01:00:12.360 --> 01:00:17.510
don't bother to really speak
up are benefiting from this.

01:00:17.510 --> 01:00:22.540
In the end of the day, it works
for them at the ground level.

01:00:22.540 --> 01:00:24.970
In other words,
the bottom line is

01:00:24.970 --> 01:00:29.570
if they all do similar things
and if it doesn't work,

01:00:29.570 --> 01:00:31.730
as they say, I'll be
gone, you'll be gone.

01:00:31.730 --> 01:00:34.610
I mean, they come
back to the industry.

01:00:34.610 --> 01:00:37.730
Everybody who borrowed too
much or took too much risk

01:00:37.730 --> 01:00:41.370
in this economy suffered
except for the bankers

01:00:41.370 --> 01:00:44.930
who took the risk and those who
were supposed to keep us safe,

01:00:44.930 --> 01:00:45.750
basically.

01:00:45.750 --> 01:00:49.340
So somehow, accountability
at the ground level

01:00:49.340 --> 01:00:51.120
is not really working.

01:00:51.120 --> 01:00:53.530
And if you work up
the governance chain,

01:00:53.530 --> 01:00:56.380
you really see the conflicted
incentives everywhere,

01:00:56.380 --> 01:00:59.600
on every level, including
even auditors, which

01:00:59.600 --> 01:01:02.560
was sort of the Enron problem.

01:01:02.560 --> 01:01:09.400
So it's kind of a depressing
note about how governance works

01:01:09.400 --> 01:01:12.370
and doesn't, but especially for
banks, it works very poorly.

